pull_request.title: Dockerfile added [skip ci]
pull_request.body: Might ease the "getting started" hurdle and circumvent possible build/setup errors. Could also be used on Windows instead of a locally built binary (rf. #36)

review.body: FWIW, LGTM. Amazing to see this test passes in 8sec when just testing Kyber* (as opposed to 2h when testing most algs...). Thanks also for updating to the "focal" image.

pull_request.title: Suppress constant time check for public matrix generation on Kyber AVX2
pull_request.body:
Fixes #1187.

* [No] Does this PR change the input/output behaviour of a cryptographic algorithm (i.e., does it change known answer test values)?  (If so, a version bump will be required from *x.y.z* to *x.(y+1).0*.)
* [No] Does this PR change the the list of algorithms available -- either adding, removing, or renaming?  (If so, PRs in OQS-OpenSSL, OQS-BoringSSL, and OQS-OpenSSH will also be required by the time this is merged.)
